I am building a modern conference landing page called "DevConf 2026" using only HTML and CSS.

The website already includes:
- Navbar
- Hero Banner
- Meet the Speakers
- Pricing Section
- Footer

I need to replace the placeholder AI section with a new section called "Why Attend DevConf?".

Design a clean and modern section that explains why developers should attend the conference.

Requirements:

Section Title:
Why Attend DevConf?

Subtitle:
Discover the experiences, knowledge, and opportunities that make DevConf 2026 the must-attend event for developers.

Create four feature cards displayed in a responsive 2×2 grid.

Each card should include:
- A simple icon (emoji or Font Awesome placeholder)
- Feature title
- A short description (1–2 sentences)

The four feature cards should be:

1. Learn from Industry Leaders
Gain practical insights from world-class engineers, founders, and technology experts.

2. Hands-on Workshops
Build real projects and improve your skills through interactive coding sessions.

3. Network with Professionals
Meet developers, recruiters, startup founders, and technology enthusiasts from around the world.

4. Career Growth
Explore internship opportunities, job openings, and mentorship sessions to accelerate your career.

Below the cards, add a centered button with the text:
Join DevConf 2026

Design Requirements:
- Use semantic HTML5
- Use only HTML and CSS (no JavaScript)
- White background
- Blue accent color (#2563EB)
- Rounded cards (16–20px)
- Soft shadows
- Smooth hover effect
- Responsive layout using CSS Grid or Flexbox
- Clean, beginner-friendly code
- The design should match the overall style of a professional technology conference website.